# Pipeline Rules

## Architecture constraints
- act_pipeline.py is the ONLY entry point. Never call sub-modules directly from app.py
- Pipeline steps execute in strict order: preprocess → normalize → retrieve → evaluate → improve → build
- Never skip retrieval step even if results are empty — empty context must still be passed downstream

## Data models
- Always use dataclasses from models.py — never pass raw dicts between pipeline steps
- ViolationContext is the central carrier object — all steps read from and write to it
- ChecklistItem is the final output — only checklist_builder.py creates it

## Error handling rules
- Every pipeline step must catch its own exceptions and log them — never let one violation crash the full batch
- If LLM returns unparseable response → log raw response + fall back to default values from config.py
- If retrieval returns 0 results → continue pipeline, set similarity score to 0.0

## What NOT to do
- Do not add new global state — pipeline_stats is already a known thread-safety problem
- Do not call Ollama directly — always go through rag_pipeline.py
- Do not hardcode thresholds — always read from config.py